"Come on people - SEED. Are there only leechers on Pirate Bay ????? "

Why is it that on every torrent there is some clueless idiot rambling about the seeder/leecher ratio. IT DOESN'T MATTER.

A seeder is merely someone sharing the entire file, while a leecher is someone who hasn't downloaded all of it yet. A leecher shares what he currently has downloaded, and it is completely irrelevant from a downloading perspective whether you are downloading from a seeder or a leecher. All that matters is whether the file is fully available.

The uploader has already seeded the file several times, which means that it IS available among the leechers (the torrent makes sure to distribute the file so that all segments of it are spread out evenly). At the moment there about 15000 seeders/leechers combined, so potentially there are 15000 people to download from. Again it doesn't matter if they are seeders or leechers.

I was downloading this at 100 kb/s within a minute from leechers only (or peers as they should be called) and it is still rising.
